definition.value: A 1-(biphenyl-4-yloxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol that is the (1S,2S)-diastereomer of bitertanol.
A flavonoid oxoanion that is the conjugate base of dalpatein, obtained by deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A 1-(biphenyl-4-yloxy)-3,3-dimethyl-1-(1,2,4-triazol-1-yl)butan-2-ol that is the (1S,2R)-diastereomer of bitertanol.
A flavonoid oxoanion that is the conjugate base of dalnigrein, obtained by deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A 26-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one in which the 25-position has S-configuration.
A 26-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one in which the 25-position has R-configuration.
A 3-ketocholest-4-en-26-al in which the 25-position has R-configuration.
A 3-ketocholest-4-en-26-al in which the 25-position has S-configuration.
A lipoyl-AMP in which the lipoyl moiety has (R)-configuration.
An androstanoid that is androst-5-ene bearing two oxo substituents at positions 3 and 17.
A sphingosine-based sphingolipid that is any N-acylsphingosine substituted at the O-1 position by a D-galactosyl residue.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as behenoyl (docosanoyl).
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxybehenoyl (2-hydroxydocosanoyl).
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as tricosanoyl
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxytricosanoyl.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as lignoceroyl (tetracosanoyl).
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is specified as 2-hydroxylignoceroyl.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-stearoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
A sulfohexosyl ceramide(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of any N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the amino function of any sphingoid
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-lignoceroyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 23 carbons and 1 double bond.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 1 double bond.
A sphingomyelin 41:1 in which the N-acyl group and sphingoid base are specified as tricosanoyl and sphingosine respectively.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.
An  organosulfonate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of torvanol A hydrogen sulfate.
A methoxyisoflavan that is isoflavan substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2', methoxy groups at positions 6 and 3', a 2-carboxyethenyl group at position 5' and a sulfoxy group at position 4.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons and 2 double bonds.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 24 carbons, 2 double bonds and a hydroxyl at C2.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is  composed of 26 carbons and 1 double bond.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 26 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons  and a hydroxy group at C2.
An N-acyl-D-galactosylsphingosine in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 25 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-icosanoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 20 carbons and 1 double bond.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) in which the ceramide N-acyl group is composed of 20 carbons, 1 double bond and a hydroxy group at C2.
A sphingomyelin in which the total number of carbons in the sphingoid base and fatty acyl groups is 41 with 1 double bond.

A polysaccharide derivative comprising a trisaccharide repeating unit consisting of N-acetyl-beta-D-mannosaminouronic acid, 3,N-diacetyl-alpha-L-fucosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-fucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->4) and (1->3), with the trisaccharide repeats themselves being linked (1->4); corresponds to the serotype 5 (CP5) capsular polysaccharide of Staphylococcus aureus.

A polysaccharide derivative comprising a trisaccharide repeating unit consisting of 4,N-diacetyl-beta-D-mannosaminouronic acid, N-acetyl-alpha-L-fucosamine and N-acetyl-beta-D-fucosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3), with the trisaccharide repeats themselves also being linked (1->3); corresponds to the serotype 8 (CP8) capsular polysaccharide of Staphylococcus aureus.
An amino disaccharide consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-L-fucosaminyl residue linked (1->3) to an N-acetyl-alpha-D-fucosamine residue.
A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alaninate(3-) in which the D-muramoyl fragment has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre; major species at pH 7.3.
An N-acyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the sulfo group of N-docosanoyl-(3-O-sulfo-D-galactosyl)sphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.
A UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate(4-) in which the muramoyl fragment has alpha-configuration at its anomeric centre; major species at pH 7.3.
